How to Create a scatter chart in Power Bi

 1.Hover your mouse on the scatter chart and  click to grab it.

2. Resize it by clicking on the icons at the edges. 

Next Steps:

Click on the ADF_Marketing_PreUserActivity_Group Table to expand it.

1. Click and drop the SessionMinuteGroupOrder column to the X-axis

2.Click and drop the PageCnGroupOrder column to the Y-axis

3.Click and drop the SessionCnt column in the Size tab

4. Click and drop the Color column in the Legend tab

-We will also use the color column to show us same day registration for Blue=1 and, Red=0  for not registering on the same day.


Editing the columns: Steps

1.  Click on the drop down tab as indicated on the arrow tab to reveal the options window

2. Select 'Don't Summarize' for X-axis SessionMinuteGroupOrder

3.Select 'Don't Summarize' for Y-axis PageCntGroupOrder

4. Select 'Count' for SessionCnt on the Size tab


Hover your mouse on the red circle to get the results below.

The red dot is red because the PreUser didn't register the same day , the PreUser spent 8 minutes on the site,  visited 3 pages and

came to our site 23 times.

Hover your mouse on the blue circle to get the results below

The Blue dot is blue because the PreUser registered the same day , the PreUser spent 7 minutes on the site,  visited 5 pages and

came to our site once.
